WEBVTT

00:06.016 --> 00:08.352
So, next weekend,
I'm going to be in Baltimore

00:08.353 --> 00:09.619
for the DA's conference,

00:09.621 --> 00:11.821
which means Grandpa is going
to stay over,

00:11.823 --> 00:14.391
so be prepared
for Westerns,

00:14.393 --> 00:15.659
and try to act interested.

00:15.661 --> 00:17.928
And you are not listening to me.

00:17.930 --> 00:20.163
Look at how cute
that little girl is.

00:23.267 --> 00:25.468
Yeah, she's adorable.

00:25.470 --> 00:27.170
Hi.

00:29.508 --> 00:30.907
Dad's kind of a jerk.

00:30.909 --> 00:33.510
Unfortunately,
that is not a crime.

00:35.212 --> 00:37.647
Five minutes ago.

00:37.649 --> 00:39.549
What do you mean?

00:39.551 --> 00:42.252
Five minutes ago,
you were that age.

00:42.254 --> 00:43.820
Feels like a hundred years ago.

00:43.822 --> 00:47.123
Hmm. Just you wait,
young lady.

00:47.125 --> 00:49.159
I know. Pretty soon,
I'll be out of school,

00:49.161 --> 00:50.593
and I'll have a job like you,

00:50.595 --> 00:52.696
and then, I'll have
a bratty kid of my own.

00:52.698 --> 00:54.965
I am just saying
that it goes by fast,

00:54.967 --> 00:57.000
so you should enjoy this age.

00:57.002 --> 00:59.469
You know what I'd really enjoy?
Hmm?

00:59.471 --> 01:01.304
If you let me stay
by myself for once

01:01.306 --> 01:02.672
when you go away
for the weekend.

01:02.674 --> 01:05.408
Finish your breakfast.

01:07.445 --> 01:09.846
I don't care what
the United Nations says.

01:09.848 --> 01:12.082
That particular nation
owes my city

01:12.084 --> 01:14.884
over $2 million
of unpaid parking tickets.

01:14.886 --> 01:16.453
Yes, sir.
Dino.

01:16.455 --> 01:19.089
Figure out some kind of
insider insult in that

01:19.091 --> 01:21.124
culture and have it delivered
to their embassy,

01:21.126 --> 01:22.425
courtesy of this office.

01:22.427 --> 01:23.860
Bad idea, Frank.

01:23.862 --> 01:25.295
Then come up with a better one.

01:25.297 --> 01:26.896
I didn't expect
to see you this morning.

01:26.898 --> 01:28.264
You told me to deliver the news

01:28.266 --> 01:30.100
even if it's not something
you want to hear.

01:30.102 --> 01:31.868
Should Garrett be in on this?

01:31.870 --> 01:33.803
Yes.

01:35.606 --> 01:38.241
The department chaplain,
Father Markham,

01:38.243 --> 01:42.245
got picked up on a DWI
about an hour ago in the 8th.

01:42.247 --> 01:43.747
At 9:00 in the morning?

01:43.749 --> 01:45.315
It's 5:00 somewhere,
as they say.

01:45.317 --> 01:46.816
Where was he stopped?

01:46.818 --> 01:48.485
This time,
on the West Side Highway.

01:48.487 --> 01:51.087
This time?
Turns out,

01:51.089 --> 01:52.922
it's the fourth time
in two months, and this morning,

01:52.924 --> 01:55.058
he rear-ended another car.
The lady was fine.

01:55.060 --> 01:57.627
She, uh, refused
medical aid at the scene.

01:57.629 --> 01:59.629
The PC's office might want
to reach out to her,

01:59.631 --> 02:00.764
make sure she's doing okay.

02:00.766 --> 02:02.766
Let legal handle it.

02:02.768 --> 02:03.900
A goodwill gesture?

02:03.902 --> 02:05.435
Could look like a cover-up.

02:05.437 --> 02:06.803
Understood.

02:06.805 --> 02:08.038
Where is he being held?

02:08.039 --> 02:09.538
Actually, he's sleeping it off

02:09.541 --> 02:11.174
in the back room at McDerry's.

02:12.544 --> 02:14.544
I'm not sure
I heard you correctly.

02:14.546 --> 02:16.312
The officer who made
the initial stop realized

02:16.314 --> 02:17.514
he was our chaplain,

02:17.516 --> 02:20.016
and he was trying
to do the right thing by him.

02:20.018 --> 02:23.987
Which is why I never heard
about the other three DWIs.

02:23.989 --> 02:25.055
Each time he got popped,

02:25.057 --> 02:26.856
it went farther up
the chain of command,

02:26.858 --> 02:29.459
and now that we have an
accident report to fill out...

02:29.461 --> 02:31.127
It landed on your desk.

02:31.129 --> 02:33.029
And now, on yours.

