02:44.708 --> 02:46.142
How's everything
over here, Erin?

02:46.144 --> 02:47.944
Delicious, as always.

02:47.946 --> 02:49.679
I'll take this
when you're ready.

02:49.681 --> 02:51.648
Thanks.

02:51.650 --> 02:54.384
So, what's the rest
of your day like?

02:54.386 --> 02:58.621
Boring class, boring class,
fun lunch.

02:58.623 --> 03:00.790
Boring class, boring class,
boring class...

03:00.792 --> 03:03.259
Okay, can you please try
to make me feel like

03:03.261 --> 03:05.795
you are ready to apply
to college next year?

03:05.797 --> 03:07.430
What in the world?!

03:07.432 --> 03:09.933
What's wrong, Ruth?

03:09.935 --> 03:13.303
That little girl
who was just here?

03:13.305 --> 03:16.639
Why would she write that?

03:17.508 --> 03:19.008
Go see if she's still outside.

03:19.010 --> 03:21.678
We knew there was something
weird with them.

03:21.680 --> 03:25.682
Okay, um, did they
pay by credit card?

03:25.684 --> 03:26.916
No. Cash.

03:37.528 --> 03:41.064
Excuse me. I'm sorry. I'm an
assistant district attorney

03:41.066 --> 03:42.432
from Manhattan.

03:42.434 --> 03:44.501
I'm wondering if anyone knew
the man who was sitting here

03:44.503 --> 03:46.569
with a little girl, or
if you had gotten a good look

03:46.571 --> 03:47.737
at his face?

03:47.739 --> 03:48.872
Mom, they're gone.

